   distribution. This emphasises the importance of temporally used
   (non-breeding) environments. For conservation planning, we thus advise
   distribution models to include all habitats used by focal species. Human
   activities may further impact a species' abundance and distribution.
   Herein, we hypothesised that increased fire frequency and anthropogenic
